#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:2
msgid "Dependencies in the development shell"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:4
msgid ""
"When [packaging software in `default.nix`](packaging-tutorial), you'll want "
"a [development environment in `shell.nix`](declarative-reproducible-envs) to "
"enter conveniently with `nix-shell` or [automatically with `direnv`](./"
"direnv)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:6
msgid ""
"How to share the package's dependencies in `default.nix` with the "
"development environment in `shell.nix`?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:8
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:10
msgid ""
"Use the [`inputsFrom` attribute to `pkgs.mkShellNoCC`](https://nixos.org/"
"manual/nixpkgs/stable/#sec-pkgs-mkShell-attributes):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:12
msgid ""
"# default.nix\n"
"let\n"
"  pkgs = import <nixpkgs> {};\n"
"  build = pkgs.callPackage ./build.nix {};\n"
"in\n"
"{\n"
"  inherit build;\n"
"  shell = pkgs.mkShellNoCC {\n"
"    inputsFrom = [ build ];\n"
"  };\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:26
msgid "Import the `shell` attribute in `shell.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:28
#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:95
msgid ""
"# shell.nix\n"
"(import ./.).shell\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:33
msgid "Complete example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:35
msgid "Assume your build is defined in `build.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:37
msgid ""
"# build.nix\n"
"{ cowsay, runCommand }:\n"
"runCommand \"cowsay-output\" { buildInputs = [ cowsay ]; } ''\n"
"  cowsay Hello, Nix! > $out\n"
"''\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:45
msgid ""
"In this example, `cowsay` is declared as a build-time dependency using "
"`buildInputs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:47
msgid "Further assume your project is defined in `default.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:49
msgid ""
"# default.nix\n"
"let\n"
"  nixpkgs = fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/"
"nixos-23.11\";\n"
"  pkgs = import nixpkgs { config = {}; overlays = []; };\n"
"in\n"
"{\n"
"  build = pkgs.callPackage ./build.nix {};\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:60
msgid "Add an attribute to `default.nix` specifying an environment:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:63
msgid ""
" let\n"
"   nixpkgs = fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/"
"nixos-23.11\";\n"
"   pkgs = import nixpkgs { config = {}; overlays = []; };\n"
" in\n"
" {\n"
"   build = pkgs.callPackage ./build.nix {};\n"
"+  shell = pkgs.mkShellNoCC {\n"
"+  };\n"
" }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:75
msgid ""
"Move the `build` attribute into the `let` binding to be able to re-use it. "
"Then take the package's dependencies into the environment with [`inputsFrom`]"
"(https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#sec-pkgs-mkShell-attributes):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:78
msgid ""
" let\n"
"   nixpkgs = fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/"
"nixos-23.11\";\n"
"   pkgs = import nixpkgs { config = {}; overlays = []; };\n"
"+  build = pkgs.callPackage ./build.nix {};\n"
" in\n"
" {\n"
"-  build = pkgs.callPackage ./build.nix {};\n"
"+  inherit build;\n"
"   shell = pkgs.mkShellNoCC {\n"
"+    inputsFrom = [ build ];\n"
"   };\n"
" }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:93
msgid "Finally, import the `shell` attribute in `shell.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:100
msgid ""
"Check the development environment, it contains the build-time dependency "
"`cowsay`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/sharing-dependencies.md:102
msgid ""
"$ nix-shell --pure\n"
"[nix-shell]$ cowsay shell.nix\n"
msgstr ""

